WEBVTT

00:03.878 --> 00:04.900
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:05.672 --> 00:06.963
I need a drink!

00:07.196 --> 00:08.482
You sound just like Dad.

00:10.001 --> 00:11.062
Dad didn't drink.

00:11.159 --> 00:14.462
Oh, no, no, I know, but your voice is deep like a man's.

00:16.551 --> 00:17.746
You want a beer?

00:17.964 --> 00:20.974
No, no. I have an audition in an hour with this great theater company,

00:21.013 --> 00:24.592
and I have to memorize a monologue from Shakespeare's Richard III.

00:24.776 --> 00:27.535
- Oh. How's that going?
- Bad.

00:29.483 --> 00:31.084
Why would you even want to do Shakespeare?

00:31.371 --> 00:33.940
Well, you know, this could be a great opportunity for me, you know?

00:33.999 --> 00:35.295
Really turn things around,

00:35.347 --> 00:37.634
get people to take me as a serious actor.

00:38.045 --> 00:39.164
Plus, I get to wear a crown.

00:41.048 --> 00:44.405
You know, maybe it would help you to memorize it if you understood the dialogue.

00:44.524 --> 00:48.211
Yeah, but it's like a whole other language.

00:48.309 --> 00:48.965
Well, let me help you.

00:49.910 --> 00:51.048
Let's start with the first line.

00:52.373 --> 00:56.003
Okay, uh, "Now is the winter of our discontent."

00:56.413 --> 00:57.359
Interesting.

00:59.039 --> 01:02.286
Uh, "made glorious summer by this sun of York."

01:02.926 --> 01:04.440
Oh, okay, sure.

01:05.657 --> 01:08.551
"And all the clouds that lowered upon our house

01:08.628 --> 01:11.534
In the deep bosom of the ocean buried."

01:17.085 --> 01:19.037
- You want to get a pizza?
- Oh, God, yes.

